<h2 id="fluid-type-scales">Fluid Type Scales</h2>

<p>Rather than using arbitrary numerical type break points, fluid type generators work with steps.</p>

<p>This is a really good explanation of the <a href="https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2017/12/building-better-ui-designs-layout-grids/">evolution of the grid</a> from the page to screens.</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2021/04/designing-developing-fluid-type-space-scales/">Smashing Magazine on Fluid Type Systems</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://utopia.fyi/type/calculator/">Utopia Fluid Type Generator</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://material.io/design/layout/understanding-layout.html#principles">Google’s layout guidelines</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Google developers use <a href="https://material.io/design/layout/pixel-density.html#density-independence"><em>density-independant pixels</em></a> as a unit of measure. It’s abbreviated as <em>dp</em> and pronounced <em>dips</em>.</p>

<p>Smashing Magazine <a href="https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2017/12/building-better-ui-designs-layout-grids/">article</a> on layout grids for different screen sizes.</p>

<p>Another <a href="https://medium.muz.li/responsive-grid-design-ultimate-guide-7aa41ca7892">good article</a> about layout grids for screens.</p>

<p><a href="https://material.io/design/typography/understanding-typography.html#type-properties">Google’s type info</a> Interesting info on aligning to the baseline grid on the screen.</p>

